sources, but how did you, A,

00:37:37.670 --> 00:37:41.600
get access to them and
then B, get them to open up

00:37:41.600 --> 00:37:46.550
and then widen your net to
people had been inside the ISIS

00:37:46.550 --> 00:37:47.950
organization where it's--

00:37:47.950 --> 00:37:49.250
&gt;&gt; Joby Warrick: Yeah.

00:37:49.250 --> 00:37:50.550
&gt;&gt; -- an astounding
piece of reporting?

00:37:50.550 --> 00:37:51.850
&gt;&gt; Joby Warrick: Well, I
appreciate that and I thank you

00:37:51.850 --> 00:37:54.640
for the reference to Lawrence
Wright's book which is he is one

00:37:54.640 --> 00:37:56.830
of my heroes and if I-- I'm

00:37:56.830 --> 00:37:59.050
in the same sentence
with him, I'm flattered.

00:37:59.050 --> 00:38:00.350
So I appreciate that.

00:38:00.350 --> 00:38:01.650
It is a difficult challenge.

00:38:01.650 --> 00:38:03.620
A part of what I think
held me was the fact

00:38:03.620 --> 00:38:06.140 position:56%
