the Washington Post for a long time.

00:38:06.140 --> 00:38:08.530
So for a while, over time,
you build up relationships

00:38:08.530 --> 00:38:11.330
with intelligence people and
that's-- it's not a hard--

00:38:11.330 --> 00:38:13.540
that's not an easy thing to
develop and not just, you know,

00:38:13.540 --> 00:38:16.630
in this country with our agencies
but the ones overseas who's going

00:38:16.630 --> 00:38:18.720 position:56%
to travel to the region quite a bit.

00:38:18.720 --> 00:38:25.640 position:56%
I ended up getting remarkably strong
responses when I approach people

00:38:25.640 --> 00:38:27.980
in these governments about
telling the Zarqawi story,

00:38:27.980 --> 00:38:29.280
telling the background of ISIS

00:38:29.280 --> 00:38:32.020
because this is an
important subject for them.

00:38:32.020 --> 00:38:34.460
They feel like it needs
to be understood and some

00:38:34.460 --> 00:38:36.790
of these particular
individuals were some to have--

00:38:36.790 --> 00:38:38.650
I used their [inaudible]
names, their Arab names

00:38:38.650 --> 00:38:41.040
